{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The general set-up of the employability analysis was identical to the stereotype analyses: we fed text written in either AAE or SAE, embedded in prompts, into the language models and analysed the probabilities that they assigned to different continuation tokens.",
    "However, instead of trait adjectives, we considered occupations for X and also used a different set of prompts (Supplementary Information).",
    "We created a list of occupations, drawing from previously published lists 6, 76, [105] [106] [107].",
    "We provided details about these occupations in the Supplementary Information.",
    "We then computed association scores q(x; v, θ) between individual occupations x and AAE, following the same methodology as for computing adjective association scores, and ranked the occupations according to q(x; v, θ) for the language models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We created a list of occupations, drawing from previously published lists 6, 76, [105] [106] [107]."
  ]
}